This paper is about a framework for Machine Reading, which involves Natural Language Understanding and Question Answering tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning models, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves evaluation of models on existing datasets, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions Link Prediction as a task, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves predicting links in a network.
